00:57:04.510 --> 00:57:15.040
[ Speaking Spanish ]

00:57:15.040 --> 00:57:16.340
Great question.

00:57:16.340 --> 00:57:18.920
&gt;&gt; Miguel Zenon: She asks
who made the decision

00:57:18.920 --> 00:57:26.170
that I was going to
become a decision.

00:57:26.170 --> 00:57:33.850
So I made that decision myself,
but it was a hard decision

00:57:33.850 --> 00:57:35.500
because at first I wasn't sure.

00:57:35.500 --> 00:57:39.100
I was like, "Maybe I
should do something else."

00:57:39.100 --> 00:57:40.740
I wanted to be an engineer.

00:57:40.740 --> 00:57:43.130
I wanted to study science and math.

00:57:43.130 --> 00:57:45.710
You know, I was interested
in that as well.

00:57:45.710 --> 00:57:49.340
But I really loved music
and I really loved to play.

00:57:49.340 --> 00:57:53.120
So I said, "I'm going to give
it a try and see how it goes.

00:57:53.120 --> 00:57:55.690
And then if after a couple
years it doesn't feel good,

00:57:55.690 --> 00:57:57.180
maybe I'll go to the other thing."

00:57:57.180 --> 00:57:58.760
It felt good after a couple
years, so I said, "Okay,

00:57:58.760 --> 00:58:00.620
I'll give it a couple more years."

00:58:00.620 --> 00:58:05.820
And then eventually I just kept
going and it became what I do.

00:58:05.820 --> 00:58:07.120
Okay?

00:58:07.120 --> 00:58:12.830
&gt;&gt; Larry Applebaum: Can you
say what you love about music?

00:58:12.830 --> 00:58:16.530
&gt;&gt; Miguel Zenon: You know, when
I first started playing music

00:58:16.530 --> 00:58:21.800
and not necessarily playing
jazz, but playing an instrument,

00:58:21.800 --> 00:58:26.410
I liked the fact that it
felt like a game to me.

00:58:26.410 --> 00:58:31.020
I remember when I was playing
music, I was also playing a lot

00:58:31.020 --> 00:58:33.270
of basketball at the time.

00:58:33.270 --> 00:58:35.100
And it felt the same way to me.

00:58:35.100 --> 00:58:37.550
It was almost like
something you do for fun.

00:58:37.550 --> 00:58:38.870
You can interact with others.

00:58:38.870 --> 00:58:42.780
You can portray your
personality, be competitive

00:58:42.780 --> 00:58:45.040
and do things to make
yourself better.

00:58:45.040 --> 00:58:49.950 position:56%
And even though I've been doing it
for a long time, I still try to find

00:58:49.950 --> 00:58:56.260
that sort of like childlike
mentality where you just do it

00:58:56.260 --> 00:58:59.200
because it's fun and playful.

00:58:59.200 --> 00:59:00.500
&gt;&gt; Larry Applebaum: Beautiful.

00:59:00.500 --> 00:59:03.150
Who else has a question?

00:59:03.150 --> 00:59:06.110
No? Well maybe now's the time.

